Vertices 16(0.33,-0.67,-0.5), 17(1,-0.67,-0.5), 18(1,-0.33,-0.5), 19(0.33,-0.33,-0.5) form the bottom row. The cylinder wall face uses vertices 1,2,10,9 - this is correct for one step. Faces like (17 18 26 25) and (18 19 27 26) also correctly reference cylinder wall areas.

